==English==

===Noun===
'''euphonium'''

===Etymology===
Derived from Greek word ''euphonos'' meaning "beautiful-sounding" 

===Meaning===

#''Music.'' A valved brass instrument, a sax horn, the tenor of the tuba family of instruments, having the appearance very similar to that of a tuba.  It is similar to and often used instead of a "Baritone" horn. (A true Baritone has a smaller bore than a Euphonium and does not sound as "full" though it covers the same range of tones.

